## File 1: Extensions/ArmClientBuilderExtensions.cs
Line 30 calls `builder.RegisterClientFactory<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions>(configuration)` which has `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode]`. 

Add `[RequiresUnreferencedCode(...)]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode(...)]` attributes to the `AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>` method. Use the same messages that `RegisterClientFactory` uses:
- For `RequiresUnreferencedCode`: "Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values is not supported with trimming. Use the Configuration Binder Source Generator (EnableConfigurationBindingGenerator=true) instead."  
- For `RequiresDynamicCode`: "Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values requires generating dynamic code at runtime, for example instantiating generic types. Use the Configuration Binder Source Generator (EnableConfigurationBindingGenerator=true) instead."

Make sure the file has `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` (it already does).

## File 2: ArmOperation.cs
The `IsResource<T>()` method at line 96-111 uses reflection (`typeof(T).GetConstructor(...)` and `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)`). The generic parameter `T` needs `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers]` annotations.

1. Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` to the `T` parameter on `IsResource<T>()`.
2. Then cascade: `Rehydrate<T>` (line 44) and `RehydrateAsync<T>` (line 82) both call `IsResource<T>()`, so add the same `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` to their `T` parameters too.

Make sure to add `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` at the top of the file.

Current `IsResource<T>` signature: `private static bool IsResource<T>() where T : notnull`
→ Change to: `private static bool IsResource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>() where T : notnull`

Current `Rehydrate<T>` signature: `public static ArmOperation<T> Rehydrate<T>(ArmClient client, RehydrationToken rehydrationToken, ArmClientOptions options = null) where T : notnull`
→ Change to: `public static ArmOperation<T> Rehydrate<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>(ArmClient client, RehydrationToken rehydrationToken, ArmClientOptions options = null) where T : notnull`

Same pattern for `RehydrateAsync<T>`.

## File 3: GenericOperationSource.cs
The class `GenericOperationSource<T>` uses `ModelReaderWriter.Read(data, typeof(T))` (which requires PublicConstructors | NonPublicConstructors on the type parameter) and `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)` (which requires NonPublicConstructors).

Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` to the `T` parameter on the class definition.

Current: `internal class GenericOperationSource<T> : IOperationSource<T>`
→ Change to: `internal class GenericOperationSource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T> : IOperationSource<T>`

The file already has `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;`.

## File 4: ArmEnvironment.cs
Line 80: `public override string ToString() => JsonSerializer.Serialize(this);`

Replace with a manual JSON construction since `ArmEnvironment` is a simple struct with `Endpoint` (Uri) and `Audience` (string):
```csharp
public override string ToString() => $"{{\"Endpoint\":\"{Endpoint}\",\"Audience\":\"{Audience}\"}}";
```

Wait, that might be fragile with special characters. A safer approach using `Utf8JsonWriter`:
```csharp
public override string ToString()
{
    var buffer = new System.Buffers.ArrayBufferWriter<byte>();
    using var writer = new Utf8JsonWriter(buffer);
    writer.WriteStartObject();
    writer.WriteString("Endpoint", Endpoint.ToString());
    writer.WriteString("Audience", Audience);
    writer.WriteString("DefaultScope", DefaultScope);
    writer.WriteEndObject();
    writer.Flush();
    return System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetString(buffer.WrittenSpan);
}
```

Actually, looking at the original, `JsonSerializer.Serialize(this)` serializes ALL public properties: Endpoint, Audience, DefaultScope. Let me use the manual Utf8JsonWriter approach. Add `using System.Buffers;` to the usings.

## File 5: ArmClientOptions.cs
Line 52: `var allProfile = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<Dictionary<string, Dictionary<string, JsonElement>>>(span);`

Replace with `JsonDocument` manual parsing:
```csharp
using var doc = JsonDocument.Parse(BinaryData.FromStream(stream));
var allProfileElement = doc.RootElement;
var armProfile = allProfileElement.GetProperty("resource-manager");
foreach (var keyValuePair in armProfile.EnumerateObject())
{
    var namespaceName = keyValuePair.Name;
    var element = keyValuePair.Value;

    foreach (var apiVersionProperty in element.EnumerateObject())
    {
        var apiVersion = apiVersionProperty.Name;
        foreach (var resourceTypeItem in apiVersionProperty.Value.EnumerateArray())
        {
            string resourceTypeName = default;
            foreach (var property in resourceTypeItem.EnumerateObject())
